1. Feature completion:
  - All planned features are implemented according to the requirements
  - User stories meet acceptance criteria
2. Code Quality:
  - Code is clean, well structured and follows agreed-upon conventions and standards
  - No severe encapsulation and extensibility practices are violated
3. Code review:
  - Peer reviewed and approved by at least one other developer
  - Feedback from reviews must be addressed
4. Testing:
  - Unit tests are written for all new functionalities
  - Unit tests must pass
  - Basic functionality must be tested
5. Documentation:
  - All code must be documented where necessary and follow self documenting code principles
